				<h1 itemprop="headline" class="entry-title">Banco Santander Profit Rises 69 Percent as Loan Provisions Decline</h1>
		<div class="story-meta-footer">
			<address class="byline author vcard" itemprop="author creator" itemtype="//schema.org/Person">
				By Chad Bray			</address>
			<!-- date published --><time class="dateline " datetime="2015-02-03T08:41:54+00:00" itemprop="datePublished">February 3, 2015 3:41 am</time>
			<!-- date updated --><span class="visually-hidden updated">February 3, 2015 3:41 am</span><button class="button comments-button  theme-kicker" data-skip-to-para-id="">
</button>
		</div>
			</header>
		<div class="entry-content">
	<div id="sharetools-story" class="sharetools theme-classic sharetools-story" data-shares="email|Email,facebook|Share,twitter|Tweet,save|Save,show-all|More,ad" data-url="https://dealbook.nytimes.com/2015/02/03/banco-santander-quarterly-profit-rises-69-percent-as-loan-provisions-decline/" data-title="Banco Santander Profit Rises 69 Percent as Loan Provisions Decline" data-description="The quarter marked a positive start for Ana Patricia BotÃ­n, who was named executive chairwoman in September.">
				<div class="ad sharetools-inline-article-ad"></div>
				<div id="MiddleLeft" class="ad middle-left-ad nocontent robots-nocontent"></div>
				</div><div class="w480"><figure class="media photo promo" itemprop="associatedMedia" itemscope="" itemid="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2015/02/04/business/04DEALTALKS2/04DEALTALKS2-blog480.jpg" itemtype="//schema.org/ImageObject" role="group"><span class="visually-hidden">Photo</span><div class="image"><img itemprop="url" itemid="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2015/02/04/business/04DEALTALKS2/04DEALTALKS2-blog480.jpg" src="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2015/02/04/business/04DEALTALKS2/04DEALTALKS2-blog480.jpg" id="100000003489853" width="480" height="320" alt="Ana Patricia Botin, chairwoman of Banco Santander."   /><meta itemprop="height" content="320"><meta itemprop="width" content="480"></div><figcaption class="caption" itemprop="description"><span class="caption-text">Ana Patricia Botin, chairwoman of Banco Santander.</span><span class="credit" itemprop="copyrightHolder"><span class="visually-hidden">Credit</span> Pablo Blazquez Dominguez/Getty Images</span></figcaption></figure></div>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">LONDON â Banco Santander of Spain reported on Tuesday that its fourth-quarter profit rose 69 percent as it continued to benefit from a decline in provisions for bad loans.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">For the three months that ended Dec. 31, Santander said profit rose to 1.46 billion euros, or about $1.7 billion, from â¬864 million in the same period a year earlier. That was slightly below analystsâ expectations, according to Reuters.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">The companyâs fourth-quarter results for 2013 were restated to reflect several accounting changes, including in how it recognizes contributions to deposit guarantee programs in Spain and in Britain.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">Santander, one of Europeâs largest banks, wrote down billions of euros in mortgages in 2013 amid a weak economy in Spain, its home market, but saw its provisions for bad loans improve over the course of last year.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">In the fourth quarter, provisions for delinquent and defaulted loans fell nearly 12 percent, to â¬2.45 billion, from the period a year earlier.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">The quarter marked a positive start for Ana Patricia BotÃ­n, a longtime Santander executive who was named executive chairwoman in September after her father, <a class="tickerized" title="More articles about Emilio Botin." href="//topics.nytimes.com/top/reference/timestopics/people/b/emilio_botin/index.html?inline=nyt-per">Emilio BotÃ­n</a>, died of a heart attack at the age of 79. Mr. BotÃ­n ran the bank for three decades.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">Since taking the reins, Ms. BotÃ­n has <a href="//dealbook.nytimes.com/2014/11/25/santander-replaces-chief-with-longtime-executive-and-shakes-up-board/">replaced the bankâs chief executive</a> and dramatically reshaped its board of directors. The bank also <a href="//dealbook.nytimes.com/2015/01/08/santander-plans-8-9-billion-capital-increase-to-strengthen-balance-sheet/">boosted its capital</a> in January by â¬7.5 billion and cut its dividend sharply in order to ease investor concerns about the strength of its balance sheet.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">For the full year, Santander said its profit rose 39 percent to â¬5.82 billion.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">Net interest income, or what a bank earns on its lending after deducting what it pays out on deposits and other liabilities, rose nearly 12 percent, to â¬7.71 billion in the fourth quarter, from â¬6.93 billion in the period a year earlier.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">Santanderâs nonperforming loan rate was 5.19 percent in the fourth quarter, about 0.09 of a percentage point lower than in the third quarter.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">Operating expenses rose 3 percent, to â¬5.22 billion in the fourth quarter.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">Santanderâs full-year earnings in Spain nearly tripled to â¬1.12 billion, up from â¬466 million in 2013, as economic conditions improved and provisions for bad loans continued to decline. For the fourth quarter, Santander posted profit of â¬299 million in its Spanish operations.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">In Britain, the bankâs profit rose 37 percent, to â¬1.58 billion in 2014, up from â¬1.15 billion in 2013. In the fourth quarter, the bank posted a profit of â¬391 million in its British business.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">In Santanderâs operations in Latin America, profit declined to â¬3.15 billion for the full year, down from â¬3.18 billion in 2013. In the fourth quarter, Santander posted a profit of â¬853 million in its Latin American business.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">The bankâs fully loaded Tier 1 capital ratio, a measure of its ability to weather financial disturbances, rose to 9.7 percent at the end of December from 8.3 percent at the end of the third quarter.</p>
	</div>
